==German==
===Etymology===
Probably a [[pars pro toto]] expression, from a very old root (related to {{Gr.}} ''phallos'' "[[penis]]"), with the related meaning "ball".
====Noun====
'''Bulle''' ''m''
# a [[bull]] (male cow)
===Etymology===
From ''(Land)Puller'', a non-derogative term for a policeman of the 18. century. In the 1960s, the term ''Bullen'' was first used by left protesters, possibly associating the American derogative term ''[[pig]]'' of that time to the animal ''[[bull]]''.

====Noun====
'''Bulle''' ''m''
# (derogative) a male [[cop]]

